titlealts.searchtitle: Data Element: FRACTION OF INSPIRED OXYGEN PERCENTAGE - Description

div.p: FRACTION OF INSPIRED OXYGEN PERCENTAGE is the result of the Clinical Investigation which measures the PERSON's fraction of inspired oxygen (FiO 2), where the UNIT OF MEASUREMENT is 'Percentage'.

For the National Neonatal Data Set - Episodic and Daily Care, FRACTION OF INSPIRED OXYGEN PERCENTAGE indicates the maximum fraction of inspired oxygen percentage that the baby received on the NEONATAL CRITICAL CARE DAILY CARE DATE.
